Module com.example.demo
Package com.example.demo.managers

Class ProjectileManager

java.lang.Object
com.example.demo.managers.ProjectileManager
public class ProjectileManager extends Object
Manages all projectiles in the game, including user and enemy projectiles.

This class tracks projectiles, handles updates and removals, and ensures proper collision management. It uses the Singleton pattern to ensure there is only one instance of the ProjectileManager.

      public void updateProjectiles()

    • removeDestroyedProjectiles

      public void removeDestroyedProjectiles()
      Removes destroyed projectiles from the scene and tracking lists. This ensures that inactive projectiles do not clutter the scene or waste resources.

    • generateEnemyProjectiles

      public void generateEnemyProjectiles(List<ActiveActorDestructible> enemies)
      Generates projectiles for enemies that are capable of firing.

      This method checks each enemy in the list and invokes their fireProjectile() method. If a projectile is fired, it is added to the scene and tracked.

      Parameters:
      enemies - The list of enemy actors capable of firing projectiles.

    • handleCollisions

      public void handleCollisions(CollisionManager collisionManager, List<ActiveActorDestructible> enemies)
      Handles collisions between projectiles and enemy units.

      Delegates collision detection to the provided CollisionManager.

      Parameters:
      collisionManager - The collision manager to handle interactions.
      enemies - The list of enemies to check for collisions.

    • clearAllProjectiles

      public void clearAllProjectiles()
      Clears all projectiles from the scene and internal tracking lists.

      This method is useful when transitioning levels or resetting the game.

    • getUserProjectiles

      public List<ActiveActorDestructible> getUserProjectiles()
      Retrieves the list of active projectiles fired by the user.

      The projectiles in this list are tracked to manage their behavior, collisions, and removal when necessary.

      Returns:
      A List of ActiveActorDestructible objects representing the user's active projectiles.

    • containsUserProjectile

      public boolean containsUserProjectile(ActiveActorDestructible projectile)
      Checks whether a specific projectile is currently in the list of user projectiles.

      This method can be used to verify if a given projectile is being tracked by the system.

      Parameters:
      projectile - The ActiveActorDestructible projectile to check.
      Returns:
      true if the projectile is in the list, false otherwise.
